7 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Opioid Abatement
Revolving Fund; making appropriations to the fund;
8 specifying amounts and source; stating purposes;
providing for noncodification; providing an effective
9 date; and declaring an emergency.
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
13 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
14 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Opioid Abatement
15 Revolving Fund created pursuant to Section 30.6 of Title 74 of the
16 Oklahoma Statutes, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from
17 the Opioid Lawsuit Settlement Fund (Fund 383) of the State Treasury,
18 the sum of Twenty Million Dollars ($20,000,000.00) to be budgeted
19 and expended in accordance with law.
20 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
21 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
22 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Opioid Abatement
23 Revolving Fund created pursuant to Section 30.6 of Title 74 of the
24 Oklahoma Statutes, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from
